The '''C-Viper series''' was a proposed modification of the [[Viper probe droid/Legends|Viper probe droid]] by [[Arakyd Industries/Legends|Arakyd Industries]]. After the success of the Viper probe droid, Arakyd sought to produce streamlined versions for the wider commercial market. Arakyd planned to replace much of the military-grade armaments and programming with commercial versions, and the droid was intended to be marketed as a [[Security droid/Legends|security droid]]. The droid was intended to be of capable of augmenting [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceport]] security forces, assisting with traffic control, analyzing cargo, pursuing criminals, and located crashed [[Starship/Legends|spacecraft]]. The C-Viper was also going to be cheaper than the Viper.<ref name="GNN14">{{JournalCite|14|Galaxywide NewsNets}}</ref>

In anticipation of sales of the C-Viper, Arakyd established a civilian sales division on [[Byblos/Legends|Byblos]] who would sell the droid once prototypes were completed. Arakyd also purchased land on [[Kelada/Legends|Kelada]] to construct a new assembly factory to produce the new droid and its components.<ref name="GNN14" />

